  "prompt": "How do I change font style in moto g 1st gen..? Is it possible?",
  "response": "To change the font style on a Moto G 1st generation, you have a few options:\n\n1. Built-in Options:\n- Go to Settings\n- Display\n- Font\n- Select available font styles (if available)\n\n2. Third-party Apps:\n- Download font-changing apps from Google Play Store\n- Examples: Font Changer, iFont, Fontster\n- These apps allow you to install and apply custom fonts\n\n3. Root Method (Advanced):\n- Requires rooting your device\n- Use root-level font-changing apps\n- More complex and risks device warranty\n\n4. Custom Launcher:\n- Some launchers like Nova Launcher offer font customization\n- Download from Play Store\n- Configure font in launcher settings\n\nNote:\n- Moto G 1st gen might have limited native font options\n- Results depend on Android version and device settings\n- Third-party apps are the easiest method\n- Always backup your device before making changes\n\nRecommendation:\n- Try third-party font-changing apps from Play Store\n- Read reviews and check compatibility\n- Proceed carefully to avoid potential issues",
